text: Sibiry Keita (born 30 January 2001) is a Malian professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for the Belgian club Eupen. ==Professional career== Keita joined the Aspire Academy in 2014, where he was one of the 3 players out of a pool of 35,200 players who tried out to join. On 31 January 2019, Keita signed a 3 year contract with Eupen. Keita made his professional debut with Eupen in a 1-0 Belgian First Division A loss to K.V.C. Westerlo on 27 April 2019. ==International career== Keita represented the Mali U17 for 2017 Africa U-17 Cup of Nations qualification. ==References== ==External links== * * AS Eupen Profile Category:2001 births Category:Living people Category:Malian footballers Category:Mali youth international footballers Category:K.A.S.
